## 17. Post-Deployment Checks

### Deployment

```bash
docker exec bmc-helix-innovation-studio bash -c "cd /workspace/sample-app && mvn clean install -Pdeploy -DskipTests"
```

- [ ] Deployment completes — look for `Final Status:Deployed` in Maven output
- [ ] No `401 Unauthorized` errors (check `developerUserName`/`developerPassword` in root `pom.xml`)
- [ ] No `Connection refused` errors (check `webUrl` in root `pom.xml` and server availability)
- [ ] Note the deployment tracking URI from the output for status monitoring

### Browser Cache Clearing (Mandatory)

- [ ] Hard refresh performed: `Cmd+Shift+R` (Mac) / `Ctrl+Shift+R` (Windows/Linux)
- [ ] If component still not visible, right-click refresh button > **"Empty Cache and Hard Reload"** (with DevTools open)
- [ ] If still stale, logout of BMC Helix > clear all browser data for the domain → login again

**Red flag**: 90% of "my deployed component doesn't show up" issues are solved by cache clearing.

### View Designer Verification

- [ ] Component appears in the View Designer component palette under the correct **group** name
- [ ] Component displays the correct **icon** and **display name**
- [ ] Component can be **dragged onto the canvas** without errors
- [ ] Design preview renders correctly (the design template HTML displays)
- [ ] No errors in browser console (F12 > Console tab) when placing the component

### Property Inspector Verification

- [ ] Right-clicking or selecting the placed component opens the property inspector
- [ ] **All custom properties** appear as controls with correct labels and tooltips
- [ ] **Standard properties** section appears (Hidden, CSS Classes, Available on devices)
- [ ] Property values can be typed/toggled and the design preview reflects changes
- [ ] Changing the `name` property updates the component label in the canvas tree
- [ ] **Save the view** — verify no validation errors block the save

### Runtime Verification

After saving the view, open it in runtime mode:

- [ ] Component renders correctly — no blank white box or missing template
- [ ] All visual elements match the runtime template and styles
- [ ] Interactive elements work (buttons, inputs, dropdowns respond to user actions)
- [ ] No JavaScript errors in the browser console
- [ ] No failed network requests in the Network tab (F12 > Network)
- [ ] If component fetches data via API, verify correct API calls are made and data displays

### Property and Action Wiring Verification

- [ ] **Hidden property**: Set `Hidden` to `true` in the property inspector; component disappears at runtime
- [ ] **Set Property action**: Create a button with a "Set Property" action targeting this component; property updates at runtime
- [ ] **Expression evaluation**: If properties have `enableExpressionEvaluation: true`, test with an expression (e.g., referencing another component's output)
- [ ] **Data dictionary**: Open the expression builder; verify component properties appear under the component's name for use in expressions

### API Integration Verification (If Applicable)

- [ ] API calls use `POST` for DataPage queries (not `GET`)
- [ ] `X-Requested-By: XMLHttpRequest` header is present on all requests (check Network tab)
- [ ] `Content-Type: application/json` header is set
- [ ] API responses return expected data structure (`data` array for DataPage)
- [ ] Error states handled gracefully — show user-friendly messages, not raw error objects
- [ ] Loading indicators display during async operations
- [ ] Empty state displays when no data is returned

### Cross-Browser / Device Check (If Time Permits)

- [ ] Component renders in Chrome, Firefox, and Edge
- [ ] If `Available on devices` is configured, component hides/shows correctly on mobile vs desktop viewports
- [ ] No horizontal scroll overflow or layout breakage at narrow widths

